cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper proposes a method to address the mode-collapse problem in the Conditional Generative Adversarial Network (cGAN) and demonstrates its effectiveness on three conditional generation tasks: image-to-image translation, image inpainting, and future video prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a regularization method for the generator, which is a common technique in machine learning, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the multi-modal nature of conditional distributions, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image and video generation, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
